    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-02T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-02T08:00:00-05:00" n="532"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d532">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 103.94/507</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-02T13:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 2, 1918, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 2.45 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2404. For <persName corresp="#p_BBM1">Baruch</persName> from <persName
                        corresp="#p_SLL1">Summers</persName>:</p>
                <p>Your 1693, September 29 [<hi rend="italic">28</hi>], my 2369 of October 1. At
                    meeting Maritime Transport Council to-day Secretary <persName corresp="#p_BND1"
                        >Baker</persName> definitely committed the United States to fully disclose
                    its shipping programme, its import programme and its programmes of all
                        kinds.<note n="1" xml:id="d532fn1">See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_533">pp. 533</ref>–<ref target="#pg_534">534</ref>.</note>
                    Understand the President authorized this. Suggest therefore that effort be made
                    to supply information through our programme committees rather than through other
                    sources.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
